			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1092">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>When I finished Poe Ballantine&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4282">The Fine Art of Quitting</a>&rdquo; [April 2009], I wondered: Is this the kind of material I want to be reading at my age (seventy-eight) &mdash; young people smoking pot and guzzling beer? Then I remembered myself at that age. We didn&rsquo;t smoke pot &mdash; though we probably would have if we&rsquo;d known about it &mdash; but we did smoke Pall Malls and Lucky Strikes and drink beer. And, like Ballantine, many of us quit college to make our own way.</p>

<p>Ballantine&rsquo;s reflections made me think of writers like John Cheever and John Steinbeck, and painters like Modigliani and Picasso: boozers all, great artists all. I am not saying that drinking, smoking, or substance abuse is a prerequisite for creativity, but it <em>is</em> common.</p>

<p>In time some of us who made our own way became writers, painters, or musicians. We still drink sometimes, though now it may only be a glass of wine as we contemplate our past.</p>

<p>I&rsquo;m no longer young or pretty, and I&rsquo;m certainly not rich and famous, but I still like to know how others see this world, even if their vision is blurred and they make their way with stumbling steps.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Shirl Brainard<br>Albuquerque, New Mexico</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1093">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I thoroughly enjoyed &ldquo;The Fine Art of Quitting,&rdquo; by Poe Ballantine. Somehow he always manages to strike a chord in me with his writing.</p>

<p>I&rsquo;ve gone to many therapists over the years, trying to sort out life or come to some kind of understanding of the world, but to no avail. Then I get <em>The Sun</em> in the mail, and I sit down and just feel a part of it all.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Kathy Jones<br>Binghamton, New York</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1024">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Thank you for Poe Ballantine&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4282/">The Fine Art of Quitting</a>&rdquo; [April 2009]. Although I have not struggled with alcohol, like him I have been struggling with my writing: specifically, starting again after a thirteen-year break. I had been toying with the idea of going back to school for an <span class="smallcaps">MFA</span> to improve my craft. And then I read Ballantine&rsquo;s wake-up call: &ldquo;I remember now why I quit [school] before. The five things you need to write well are talent, heart, life experience, persistence, and luck, and the university can&rsquo;t give you one of them. And if I stayed in school what would I write about? What would the other students&rsquo; beloved Kerouac have written if he&rsquo;d spent his youth hiding out in college: <em>My Trip to the Water Fountain</em>?&rdquo;</p>

<p>I intend to work at living life instead of hiding in workshops and classrooms.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Liz Fiscus<br>Independence, Missouri</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

				<div class="text-center">
			<button class="b b-1 xsmall js-b-readmore-correspondence" data-collapsible="#article-correspondences" data-label="Read More Letters">Read More Letters</button>
		</div>
			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
			</div>
			<a href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor" class="cta-button b b-4 b-padding-tight small" data-label="Write Us A Letter!">Write Us A Letter!</a>
		</div>
	</div>
	

